            1
            
              
                x
                
                  2
                
              
              +
              1
            
          
        
        =
        0.
      
    
    {\displaystyle \lim _{x\to -\infty }{\frac {1}{x^{2}+1}}=\lim _{x\to +\infty }{\frac {1}{x^{2}+1}}=0.}
  Other common functions that have one or two horizontal asymptotes include x ↦ 1/x (that has an hyperbola as it graph), the Gaussian function 
  
    
      
